#
# P10-FIX-E: CODEOWNERS for files where a malicious or careless PR
# can subvert the gateway/TEE production hardening. Branch protection
# on `main` MUST require code-owner review for these patterns — that's
# the policy hook that prevents one reviewer from approving a PR that
# both removes the `compile_error!` gate AND amends the CI strings
# check in the same change.
#
# Until a real maintainer set is in place, every entry routes to
# `@ullm-security` (a placeholder team handle). Replace with the real
# GitHub team handle before enabling CODEOWNERS on the production
# repo, and configure branch protection to require approval from this
# CODEOWNERS file.

# === Compile-time hardening gates ===
# `dev-keys` vs `prod` mutual-exclusion `compile_error!` lines.
# Removing or weakening these would silently re-enable the dev
# endpoint in a "prod" build.
crates/ullm-gateway/src/lib.rs   @ullm-security
crates/ullm-tee/src/lib.rs       @ullm-security

# === CI gates ===
# The release-promotion strings-check + feature-matrix definitions
# live here. Modifications require security review.
.github/workflows/ci.yml         @ullm-security
.github/CODEOWNERS               @ullm-security

# === Security-critical crates ===
# Crypto, attestation, transparency-log, and shutdown surfaces.
crates/ullm-core/src/shutdown.rs      @ullm-security
crates/ullm-crypto/                   @ullm-security
crates/ullm-handshake/                @ullm-security
crates/ullm-attest/                   @ullm-security
crates/ullm-transparency/             @ullm-security
crates/ullm-tee/src/nonce_registry.rs @ullm-security
crates/ullm-tee/src/tenant.rs         @ullm-security
crates/ullm-gateway/src/rate_limit.rs @ullm-security
crates/ullm-gateway/src/proxy.rs      @ullm-security

# === Security policy ===
SECURITY.md                       @ullm-security
CHANGELOG.md                      @ullm-security
docs/OPERATIONS.md                @ullm-security
docs/audit/                       @ullm-security

# === Build-reproducibility infra ===
# A tampered flake.nix could publish a non-reproducible image with
# tampered measurements — review every change.
infra/                            @ullm-security
Cargo.toml                        @ullm-security
Cargo.lock                        @ullm-security
